    • Field Detail

      • DEFAULT_INSTANCE

        public static final TimestampConverter DEFAULT_INSTANCE
        This instance can be used for getting a default instance of a timestamp converter. It is similar to the Singleton Design Pattern (for further details see Creational Patterns, Prototype in Design Patterns: Elements of Reusable Object-Oriented Software by Erich Gamma, Richard Helm, Ralph Johnson, and John Vlissides) except that there are no mechanisms to avoid the creation of other instances of a timestamp converter.

      • SIZE

        public static final int SIZE
        This field contains the number of bytes needed to serialize the long value of a Timestamp object. Because this size is predefined it must not be measured each time.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
